iption":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"darthdeus","user_is_author":true,"tags":["programming"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/jiqeom","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/jiqeom/is_simple_actually_good"},{"short_id":"dhogio","created_at":"2026-03-21T04:38:09.000-05:00","title":"Thoughts on OpenAI acquiring Astral and uv/ruff/ty","url":"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Mar/19/openai-acquiring-astral/","score":25,"flags":8,"comment_count":4,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"fuzzy","user_is_author":false,"tags":["python"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dhogio","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dhogio/thoughts_on_openai_acquiring_astral_uv"},{"short_id":"d5nvf5","created_at":"2026-03-21T01:14:17.000-05:00","title":"H\u0026R Block tax software installs a TLS root certificate with bundled private key","url":"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47457162","score":16,"flags":3,"comment_count":3,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"jmillikin","user_is_author":false,"tags":["security"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/d5nvf5","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/d5nvf5/h_r_block_tax_software_installs_tls_root"},{"short_id":"dttagp","created_at":"2026-03-20T23:23:02.000-05:00","title":"Unix philosophy is dead! Long live... something else?","url":"https://sdomi.pl/weblog/27-manifesto-of-a-burnt-out-hacker/","score":28,"flags":1,"comment_count":16,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"FedericoSchonborn","user_is_author":false,"tags":["rant"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dttagp","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dttagp/unix_philosophy_is_dead_long_live"},{"short_id":"vvt1fh","created_at":"2026-03-20T21:27:43.000-05:00","title":"What creative technical outlets of yours have been ruined by generative AI?","url":"","score":53,"flags":1,"comment_count":24,"description":"\u003cp\u003eI'm watching over my alma mater's \u003ca href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capture_the_flag_(cybersecurity)\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ecapture the flag\u003c/a\u003e event, and wow, it is dire. This used to be a creative outlet for me and an educational opportunity for students, but now it's almost entirely uncritical use of genAI tools; challenge developers now are \"hardening\" their challenges against this, but this makes it totally inaccessible to new players, so it's losing its educational value and enjoyability as well. As a developer, why should I put any creative effort in when I know it's just going to be churned by a machine and not enjoyed by anyone?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePerhaps I just want to commiserate, but I'm also genuinely curious: what outlets for you have been affected similarly by this new wave?\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"I'm watching over my alma mater's [capture the flag](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capture_the_flag_(cybersecurity)) event, and wow, it is dire. This used to be a creative outlet for me and an educational opportunity for students, but now it's almost entirely uncritical use of genAI tools; challenge developers now are \"hardening\" their challenges against this, but this makes it totally inaccessible to new players, so it's losing its educational value and enjoyability as well. As a developer, why should I put any creative effort in when I know it's just going to be churned by a machine and not enjoyed by anyone?\r\n\r\nPerhaps I just want to commiserate, but I'm also genuinely curious: what outlets for you have been affected similarly by this new wave?","submitter_user":"addison","user_is_author":true,"tags":["ask","vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/vvt1fh","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/vvt1fh/what_creative_technical_outlets_yours"},{"short_id":"hvq58r","created_at":"2026-03-20T19:11:38.000-05:00","title":"Looking at Unity finally made me understand the point of C++ coroutines","url":"https://mropert.github.io/2026/03/20/unity_cpp_coroutines/","score":7,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":""